WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:07.007
♪

00:16.015 --> 00:18.435
Am I shiny?
I don't wanna be shiny.

00:18.435 --> 00:19.353
PRODUCTION ASSISTANT:
One minute, Miss Alexander.

00:19.353 --> 00:20.896
Yes. Okay. Thank you.
[cell phone ringing]

00:23.565 --> 00:26.068
<i>Hi, honey. I'm about to do my TED Talk.</i>

00:26.068 --> 00:27.653
- Mom?
- Yes?

00:27.653 --> 00:29.404
FINN:
<i>Don't freak out, please.</i>

00:31.198 --> 00:32.366
Grandpa got arrested.

00:32.366 --> 00:34.034
What? No. No, no, no, no, no.

00:34.034 --> 00:35.869
What do you mean?
Where are you? Are you okay?

00:35.869 --> 00:36.703
FINN:
<i>I'm fine.</i>

00:36.703 --> 00:38.997
The cops brought me home,
but they took Grandpa downtown.

00:38.997 --> 00:39.957
PRODUCTION ASSISTANT:
Miss Alexander?

00:39.957 --> 00:41.834
Yes.
Okay. Yes.

00:41.834 --> 00:43.126
I'm sorry. I just have to, um--

00:43.126 --> 00:45.295
<i>Finn, I'm glad that you're okay.</i>

00:45.295 --> 00:47.756
And I will call you
as soon as this is done.

00:48.340 --> 00:49.174
Okay?

00:55.514 --> 00:57.266
♪

00:57.266 --> 00:58.267
[exhales]

00:58.267 --> 01:02.479
♪

01:02.479 --> 01:03.313
OFFICER:
<i>Next.</i>

01:07.693 --> 01:10.821
♪

01:14.074 --> 01:15.826
[audience applauding]
PAIGE: <i>Oh.</i>

01:15.826 --> 01:17.619
[cheering]
[chuckles] Thank you.

01:17.619 --> 01:19.204
♪

01:19.204 --> 01:22.916
Um, welcome to this TED Talk.

01:23.959 --> 01:28.589
Um, so let's talk about
How To Fix Your Picker.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.048
[woman giggles]
Okay?

01:30.048 --> 01:31.383
[scattered laughter]

01:32.176 --> 01:33.635
This is a woodpecker.

01:34.136 --> 01:35.804
See? Right there.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.099
And he's up there because I used to be

01:39.099 --> 01:41.810
really, really bad at picking peckers.

01:41.810 --> 01:43.395
[all chuckle]

01:43.395 --> 01:44.563
Okay.

01:44.938 --> 01:47.274
Um, but I don't--

01:49.359 --> 01:51.195
Uh, I'm not--

01:55.532 --> 01:57.659
[exhales]
I-I don't, um--

02:01.413 --> 02:03.040
Something just happened.

02:04.541 --> 02:05.375
And, um--

02:05.375 --> 02:06.502
Okay.

02:07.711 --> 02:08.754
I'm just gonna--

02:08.754 --> 02:11.215
I'm just gonna get
very real with you all.

02:12.007 --> 02:12.841
Um--

02:13.550 --> 02:16.887
One minute ago
I got a call that my dad,

02:18.347 --> 02:19.681
who is on parole,

02:21.099 --> 02:23.393
and who lives with me and my son,

02:23.393 --> 02:27.773
after spending 17 years
in a federal prison,

02:30.442 --> 02:32.444
Is under arrest.

02:34.404 --> 02:35.864
You know, people always say

02:35.864 --> 02:39.576
that your parents do the best
that they can.

02:40.911 --> 02:43.121
What I'm-- What I'm trying to figure out

02:43.914 --> 02:46.041
in this very moment is

02:48.126 --> 02:52.256
what do you owe a parent
whose best wasn't good enough?

02:52.256 --> 02:55.551
♪

02:55.551 --> 02:57.302
So let's talk about that.

02:58.262 --> 03:03.267
♪

03:03.267 --> 03:06.770
EDWIN:
<i>Mockingbird don’t sing ♪</i>

03:06.770 --> 03:11.275
<i>♪ She's gonna buy me a diamond ring ♪</i>

03:11.275 --> 03:12.359
Oh, God, no.

03:12.818 --> 03:15.070
Morning.
[Paige sighs deeply]

03:15.070 --> 03:17.197
No, stop. Please. Really?

03:17.197 --> 03:18.657
You gonna come get me out?

03:19.199 --> 03:21.243
No, not today.

03:21.243 --> 03:22.244
EDWIN:
You sure now?

03:22.244 --> 03:24.997
'Cause I think
you kinda like having me here.

03:25.873 --> 03:27.583
And I think you wanna come get me.

03:27.583 --> 03:28.542
No.

03:31.295 --> 03:32.921
Who do you think you are?

03:32.921 --> 03:34.798
Your subconscious obviously.

03:35.841 --> 03:37.843
[grunts softly]

03:37.843 --> 03:39.887
See, this is your psychology shit, mama.

03:41.263 --> 03:43.056
Live by the couch, die by the couch.

03:44.391 --> 03:45.934
Of course, I feel guilty.

03:46.935 --> 03:50.731
A daughter is supposed
to bail her dad out of jail.

03:50.731 --> 03:54.276
That's like chapter one
in the <i>My Dad's In Jail</i> handbook.

03:54.276 --> 03:56.320
I did not know you read that book.

03:56.320 --> 03:57.154
I skimmed it.

04:01.700 --> 04:02.993
Paigey, Paigey.

04:04.912 --> 04:06.121
[sighs]

04:06.121 --> 04:08.165
No. No, no.

04:11.627 --> 04:14.129
I'm not getting you out of jail.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.882
I do not owe you that.

04:16.882 --> 04:17.883
[sighs]

04:18.926 --> 04:21.261
I am gonna have my Wednesday

04:22.554 --> 04:24.640
because that is what I owe myself.

04:24.640 --> 04:25.557
EDWIN:
Well, okay.

04:26.225 --> 04:28.727
Then don't let me stand in your way.

04:29.478 --> 04:32.773
You go and you live your Wednesday.

04:32.773 --> 04:35.108
I will. Thank you.

04:35.108 --> 04:36.735
You are more than welcome.

04:37.194 --> 04:40.155
You're very polite for a subconscious.

04:40.155 --> 04:41.156
EDWIN:
Manners.

04:41.156 --> 04:43.534
Very important.
I always told you that, Paige.

04:44.076 --> 04:45.202
Manners.

04:45.202 --> 04:48.914
♪

04:51.375 --> 04:52.793
[Paige sighs]

04:52.793 --> 04:54.628
- Mom.
- Hey.

04:54.628 --> 04:55.712
We have to go get Grandpa.

04:55.712 --> 04:56.755
PAIGE:
Oh, God.

04:56.755 --> 04:59.591
We went over this last night, Finn.
I am not getting him out.

04:59.591 --> 05:00.467
Why not?

05:00.467 --> 05:04.555
Because I gave him one chance,
he betrayed me.

05:04.555 --> 05:06.098
FINN:
But it was my fault.

05:06.098 --> 05:07.474
No.
FINN: I should have been driving.

05:07.474 --> 05:09.852
No. Do not blame yourself.
It is not your fault.

05:09.852 --> 05:11.687
It's the one time I asked him to drive.

05:11.687 --> 05:13.188
PAIGE:
No, it's not the one time.

05:13.188 --> 05:16.859
It is every single time
that has led up to this one time.

05:16.859 --> 05:18.026
Why are you like this?

05:18.026 --> 05:21.363
Because, Finn, I've seen this movie
and I know how it ends.

05:21.363 --> 05:23.574
Spoiler alert, somebody dies in the end.

05:23.574 --> 05:25.409
And that somebody
is the part of you that trusts people.

05:25.409 --> 05:27.369
- Imma go visit him then.
- No!

05:29.329 --> 05:32.207
Absolutely not.
You are not going to a jail.

05:33.959 --> 05:34.793
[scoffs]

05:35.294 --> 05:37.838
Also, you have to be 18
to go by yourself, so-- Heh.

05:38.755 --> 05:39.798
- Really?
- Yeah.

05:41.800 --> 05:43.343
- You won't even visit?
- Nope.

05:43.719 --> 05:46.972
I am going to live my Wednesday!

05:48.098 --> 05:49.558
I'm going to spin.

05:51.685 --> 05:52.644
What are you doing today?

05:52.644 --> 05:54.438
- You're going to spin?
- I am.

05:54.938 --> 05:56.440
FINN:
Well, enjoy your Wednesday.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.442
Where are you going?
Where are you going?

05:58.442 --> 06:00.277
Where are you going? Where are you going?
Where are you going?

06:00.277 --> 06:01.987
[dial tone]

06:01.987 --> 06:04.031
[indistinct chatter in distance]

06:11.747 --> 06:13.040
PRISONER:
Yo, man, you going to call someone

06:13.040 --> 06:14.166
or just stand there?

06:14.708 --> 06:16.543
I’ll call who I want
and I’ll stand where I want.

06:16.543 --> 06:17.711
You understand, youngblood?

06:24.718 --> 06:26.595
Sorry, man. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

06:27.137 --> 06:28.430
Go-go ahead.

06:32.059 --> 06:34.186
♪

06:34.186 --> 06:37.856
This is your life, people.
You're unstoppable!

06:37.856 --> 06:40.442
Yes, I'm unstoppable!

06:40.442 --> 06:41.610
- You are?
- Yes!

06:41.610 --> 06:43.529
I'm definitely stoppable.

06:43.529 --> 06:45.739
Like I'm gonna stop right now.

06:45.739 --> 06:47.741
No!
[panting]

06:47.741 --> 06:50.118
Let's go, bitches. No stopping!

06:50.118 --> 06:51.954
I'm right there with you, baby girl!

06:51.954 --> 06:55.874
Can’t stop, won’t stop!
Never gonna leave you, girl!

06:55.874 --> 06:57.376
Come on, baby. Whoo!

06:57.376 --> 06:58.252
[screams]

06:58.252 --> 06:59.127
Whoo!

06:59.127 --> 07:01.255
[screaming]
Yeah, girl, you got this!

07:01.255 --> 07:02.172
Whoo!

07:02.172 --> 07:04.007
No, no, no, no, no!

07:04.883 --> 07:07.511
[indistinct announcement over PA]

07:07.511 --> 07:08.637
[woman sighs]

07:13.976 --> 07:15.394
Oh, now you're just flirting.

07:19.231 --> 07:20.190
Thank you.

07:22.526 --> 07:23.402
You alright?

07:23.861 --> 07:24.820
I guess.

07:25.779 --> 07:27.281
I'm surprised your mom let you come.

07:27.739 --> 07:29.199
She hated this growing up.

07:29.199 --> 07:31.785
Yeah, well, two different people.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.416
You go first, sweetie.

07:38.500 --> 07:39.543
I'll be right here.

07:39.543 --> 07:41.545
[indistinct announcement over PA]

07:43.130 --> 07:44.298
- Okay.
- Okay.

07:47.593 --> 07:48.594
[sighs]

07:49.386 --> 07:50.554
♪

07:50.554 --> 07:52.931
PAIGE:
I'm just having a really bad day.

07:52.931 --> 07:55.976
How can that be?
You are a TED Talker now.

07:55.976 --> 07:57.686
- Oh.
- How'd it go?

07:57.686 --> 07:59.354
Uh, it went, you know,
I said some things,

07:59.354 --> 08:00.689
not what I planned to say,
but I said them.

08:00.689 --> 08:03.150
People liked them, I guess.
I don't know. How would I know?

08:03.150 --> 08:05.110
Because they either booed or clapped.

08:05.110 --> 08:06.361
Real simple.

08:06.361 --> 08:07.863
EDWIN:
Mm! Mm!

08:07.863 --> 08:10.574
[Paige gasps]
Now that is a jammy cab.

08:13.410 --> 08:14.828
I saw your TED Talk.

08:15.495 --> 08:16.580
You were so good.

08:17.623 --> 08:19.208
But I have one question, Paige.

08:20.250 --> 08:24.338
I mean, girl,
you were so honest up there, baby girl.

08:25.797 --> 08:28.217
Then why you keep lying to my boy Mal?

08:29.301 --> 08:33.305
Why you can't be that honest with Mal?

08:35.474 --> 08:37.893
Uh... fuck.

08:37.893 --> 08:38.894
Okay. Um--

08:40.604 --> 08:42.689
Esti, can I tell you something
without you judging me?

08:42.689 --> 08:44.441
- Of course.
- Okay.

08:44.441 --> 08:45.776
I slept with Bill.

08:45.776 --> 08:47.027
What the fuck is wrong with you?

08:47.027 --> 08:49.196
What? You said you would not judge me.

08:49.196 --> 08:50.864
Did I? I don't recall.
PAIGE: Yes.

08:50.864 --> 08:54.660
Oh. Also, I think
I have to break up with Mal.

08:54.660 --> 08:56.119
Okay. Paige, slow down.

08:56.119 --> 08:58.247
I-I think you span too hard. "Span"?

08:58.247 --> 08:59.581
- Spin?
- Spun?

08:59.581 --> 09:02.960
The point is, exercise is dangerous,
and we're never doing it again.

09:02.960 --> 09:05.128
And you cannot break up with Mal.

09:05.128 --> 09:06.755
He is too fine to break up with.

09:06.755 --> 09:08.048
You haven't even heard the worst thing.

09:09.007 --> 09:12.553
My dad got arrested,
and he's still in jail.

09:12.553 --> 09:15.055
Ohh! I know.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.015
Paige, and you're just,
you're sitting here

09:17.015 --> 09:19.726
spanning, spinning, spunning
and drinking wine?

09:19.726 --> 09:22.604
Okay, what-what the fuck are you thinking?
Do you see this?

09:22.604 --> 09:24.273
This is my "what the fuck
are you thinking" face.

09:24.273 --> 09:27.150
I'm thinking that he obviously did
something he promised he wouldn't do.

09:27.150 --> 09:29.653
So I have to do what I promised
I would do when he did that thing.

09:29.653 --> 09:30.988
Like let him rot in jail?

09:30.988 --> 09:33.740
Um, yeah. Is that so bad?

09:34.658 --> 09:36.326
Uh, yeah?

09:36.326 --> 09:38.120
Ugh.
[cell door buzzes]

09:53.844 --> 09:54.803
Hi, Grandpa.

09:54.803 --> 09:55.888
Hey, Finneas.

09:58.140 --> 10:00.309
You know, I'm not sure

10:00.309 --> 10:01.977
your grandma should have
brought you out here, man.

10:04.271 --> 10:07.608
I don't want you seein' me like this,
you know, locked up.

10:09.818 --> 10:11.028
Not good for you, son.

10:11.028 --> 10:13.238
Oh, do you mean like adult content?

10:13.238 --> 10:14.156
That doesn't bother me.

10:14.865 --> 10:15.699
Yeah.

10:18.493 --> 10:19.828
How's your mama doing?

10:19.828 --> 10:20.829
She's doing alright?

10:22.581 --> 10:24.249
Oh, man, man, man.

10:24.917 --> 10:27.419
I have gone and done exactly

10:28.378 --> 10:30.005
what she was most afraid of, Finn.

10:30.005 --> 10:33.008
Driving without a license is, like,
not even that big of a deal.

10:33.008 --> 10:34.176
EDWIN:
I should have known better.

10:35.052 --> 10:36.178
I made a mess.

10:37.596 --> 10:38.680
I hurt your mama.

10:40.182 --> 10:41.558
And I hurt you.

10:41.558 --> 10:44.102
No. We need to get you outta here.

10:44.102 --> 10:45.812
I am not your problem.

10:46.647 --> 10:49.441
Do not worry about me.

10:49.441 --> 10:50.484
I'm not worried.

10:51.443 --> 10:53.946
It's actually more of a strategy question.

10:53.946 --> 10:55.948
Because, you know, I'm a gamer.

10:58.450 --> 11:01.620
♪

11:01.620 --> 11:03.539
Yeah, you are.
FINN: So--

11:05.582 --> 11:07.084
How do we defeat jail?

11:07.626 --> 11:12.881
♪

11:18.303 --> 11:20.222
So what did he do?

11:20.222 --> 11:22.558
I don't know. He got arrested.

11:23.016 --> 11:23.851
That's what he did.

11:23.851 --> 11:25.394
It matters what for.

11:25.394 --> 11:26.979
Oh, really? Does it, though?

11:26.979 --> 11:29.731
Yeah, of course, it does.
What if he's not guilty of anything?

11:29.731 --> 11:30.858
WOMAN:
Oh, my gosh.

11:31.400 --> 11:33.026
Are you the one with the TED Talk?

11:33.026 --> 11:34.528
About your bad dad?

11:34.528 --> 11:35.362
Oh.

11:36.613 --> 11:37.823
Uh-- Wow.

11:37.823 --> 11:39.783
- Were you there?
- On Twitter?

11:39.783 --> 11:41.201
Girl, I was so moved.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.954
PAIGE:
Oh. Oh, thank-- Thank you. What are you--

11:43.954 --> 11:45.038
What is she talking about?

11:45.622 --> 11:46.832
Bitch?
PAIGE: What?

11:46.832 --> 11:47.833
You're going viral.

11:47.833 --> 11:49.376
Huh? What? Are you kidding?

11:51.003 --> 11:52.546
What is-- What is happening?

11:52.546 --> 11:54.214
You have over 71,000 views.

11:54.214 --> 11:56.758
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. What do I do?

11:56.758 --> 11:59.094
Get your shit together
'cause you're blowin' up, girl.

11:59.094 --> 11:59.970
Um--

12:01.722 --> 12:03.557
Esti, I love you very much.

12:04.016 --> 12:05.767
But I have to go talk to Mal.

12:06.310 --> 12:08.687
- Bye. You can--
- Uh, yeah, I got it.

12:09.313 --> 12:10.522
PAIGE: Thank you.
ESTI: Thank you.

12:10.522 --> 12:11.773
- PAIGE: Bye.
- Bye.

12:14.401 --> 12:20.115
♪

12:20.866 --> 12:23.452
I'm so sorry to drop in
on you like this.

12:23.452 --> 12:26.538
I know. I got the notification
your dad was picked up.

12:26.538 --> 12:29.958
Technically I can’t tell you that,
but I just did, so--

12:30.959 --> 12:31.877
How are you?

12:32.419 --> 12:34.880
Uh, I'm alright, I guess.

12:34.880 --> 12:35.964
So how's your dad?

12:36.465 --> 12:38.759
I'm not actually sure how he is.

12:38.759 --> 12:40.844
Uh, I haven't spoken to him.

12:42.262 --> 12:43.305
Huh.

12:43.305 --> 12:46.141
So you haven't gotten him out yet?

12:46.600 --> 12:48.769
No. And I'm not planning to.

12:49.520 --> 12:51.396
But also, I need to tell you something.

12:52.940 --> 12:54.149
Uh--

12:54.608 --> 12:55.442
Um--

12:57.653 --> 12:59.446
I had sex with Bill.

13:00.489 --> 13:01.698
Oh.

13:01.698 --> 13:02.908
Wow. Um--

13:04.201 --> 13:07.871
Okay. I was not expecting that.

13:07.871 --> 13:09.206
Me neither.

13:09.206 --> 13:10.207
Um--

13:10.666 --> 13:13.043
And I didn't do it
because I wanna be with him.

13:13.043 --> 13:16.463
You know, I did it because
I'm just really trying to figure out

13:16.463 --> 13:19.466
who I am and what I need.

13:19.967 --> 13:22.845
And this is how you go about it?

13:22.845 --> 13:23.846
Um--

13:27.599 --> 13:28.725
[sighs]

13:28.725 --> 13:30.394
So we're done.

13:30.394 --> 13:32.563
I wanna be in love with you.

13:32.563 --> 13:36.984
I feel like I should be in love with you
because you're so good.

13:36.984 --> 13:38.902
You're so wonderful.

13:38.902 --> 13:39.862
I hope that you know that.

13:39.862 --> 13:44.491
That-that there is literally nothing wrong
with you whatsoever at all ever.

13:44.491 --> 13:46.201
But I'm, uh--

13:46.201 --> 13:48.829
♪

13:48.829 --> 13:51.123
Hmm. I'm-I'm just not there.

13:52.624 --> 13:54.418
Paige, this is about your dad.

13:55.627 --> 13:57.171
Okay? He got arrested.

13:57.171 --> 13:58.839
And now you're reacting.

13:58.839 --> 14:02.301
No, no, it's not about my dad.

14:03.177 --> 14:06.930
I mean, yes, him getting out
and coming to live with me

14:06.930 --> 14:10.350
and now getting arrested
has made it super-duper clear

14:10.350 --> 14:12.978
that every choice I've ever made
in every relationship

14:12.978 --> 14:14.313
is really because I've never dealt--

14:14.730 --> 14:16.148
Oh, my God. Yeah.

14:16.815 --> 14:20.694
Yeah, you're right. It's maybe
a little bit about my dad, but--

14:20.694 --> 14:24.615
Yeah, yeah, I don't know
if you believe this or not,

14:25.282 --> 14:27.993
but you deserve to be with somebody great.

14:27.993 --> 14:29.244
You really do.

14:29.244 --> 14:31.121
But no one great
is gonna put up with any of this.

14:31.121 --> 14:33.373
So, whatever you have going on,

14:34.583 --> 14:35.876
I hope you figure it out.

14:41.757 --> 14:47.763
♪

14:54.228 --> 14:55.103
[doorknob rattles]

14:57.105 --> 14:58.106
PAIGE:
Where have you been?

14:58.106 --> 14:59.525
Oh, I'm going to my room.

14:59.525 --> 15:01.610
What's happening? Why are you here?

15:01.610 --> 15:03.070
He asked me to take him.

15:03.070 --> 15:04.029
Take him where?

15:05.280 --> 15:06.448
NADINE: Ugh.

15:06.448 --> 15:07.824
Did you take my son to jail?

15:07.824 --> 15:10.369
Paige.
I thought it was okay with you.

15:10.369 --> 15:12.037
What would make you think that?

15:12.037 --> 15:14.873
All of our happy memories
visiting Leavenworth?

15:14.873 --> 15:15.999
Finn!

15:17.835 --> 15:19.545
Finn, get down here!

15:22.631 --> 15:24.925
You went to jail without my permission?

15:24.925 --> 15:26.802
Yeah. And I'm glad I did.

15:28.136 --> 15:29.763
Hope you enjoyed your Wednesday.

15:36.436 --> 15:37.437
How could you?

15:38.438 --> 15:43.944
This is the one thing
I never wanted my child to experience.

15:43.944 --> 15:45.946
The one thing!

15:45.946 --> 15:48.532
Oh, I know it was hard for you.

15:48.532 --> 15:50.367
Oh, God.
NADINE: I was there, Paige.

15:51.368 --> 15:52.995
And it was hard for me, too.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.497
I think that you should go.

15:57.583 --> 15:58.458
Bye, Finn.

16:00.002 --> 16:02.421
[door opens, closes]

16:02.838 --> 16:04.715
YOUNG PAIGE:
Can you believe this bitch?

16:04.715 --> 16:06.758
She's trying to tell you
she knows how you feel?

16:07.217 --> 16:10.053
But, sorry, her dad wasn't in jail.

16:10.596 --> 16:12.306
Her boyfriend was.

16:12.306 --> 16:14.850
And you can leave a boyfriend
anytime you want.

16:15.601 --> 16:16.852
But a dad?

16:18.020 --> 16:20.063
You're stuck with him forever.

16:20.814 --> 16:21.773
Wait, wait. Stop.

16:21.773 --> 16:23.859
You stop. I'm ranting.

16:24.943 --> 16:29.489
No, no, I'm just getting something
that I wasn't getting before.

16:30.574 --> 16:32.034
I think that I need to talk to you.

16:32.034 --> 16:34.703
I think that there are things
that you need me to say

16:34.703 --> 16:36.538
in order for you to feel safe.

16:37.748 --> 16:39.416
I'm listening.

16:39.416 --> 16:40.334
PAIGE:
Oh, man.

16:41.418 --> 16:44.963
I'm so sorry for everything
that you've been through.

16:45.631 --> 16:47.508
That your mama left you

16:48.300 --> 16:50.844
and you had to stay
in all those foster homes.

16:51.345 --> 16:53.055
That your dad went to prison.

16:53.931 --> 16:59.019
And I am double, triple sorry
that I have not been there for you

16:59.019 --> 17:00.812
in the way that I should have.

17:00.812 --> 17:01.730
Come here.

17:01.730 --> 17:07.528
♪

17:07.528 --> 17:09.488
People are going to leave you.

17:09.488 --> 17:11.114
♪

17:11.114 --> 17:11.990
But...

17:13.617 --> 17:18.330
I will never ever leave you again.

17:19.581 --> 17:22.501
So you can relax.

17:23.377 --> 17:24.378
Okay?

17:24.795 --> 17:28.215
You can go play. Go be a kid.

17:28.215 --> 17:30.133
You don't-- You don't have to
take care of me anymore

17:30.133 --> 17:33.095
because I'm gonna take care of you.

17:33.095 --> 17:35.472
♪

17:35.472 --> 17:36.515
YOUNG PAIGE: [chuckling]
Okay.

17:36.515 --> 17:39.518
