18:10.883 --> 18:11.800
FINN:
<i>So what changed?</i>

18:12.384 --> 18:14.720
Um, I just decided
I wanted to be the kind of person

18:14.720 --> 18:15.888
who got my dad out of jail

18:15.888 --> 18:18.182
more than I wanted to be
the kind of person who didn't.

18:19.391 --> 18:20.225
Hi.

18:21.810 --> 18:24.271
We're here to post bail
for Edwin Alexander.

18:24.855 --> 18:26.023
[keyboard keys clack]

18:26.440 --> 18:29.109
Says here he was discharged at 4:36 p.m.

18:29.109 --> 18:30.569
Can they just do that?

18:31.153 --> 18:33.780
They can if someone who
knows someone makes a call.

18:37.826 --> 18:39.244
Okay, he's out. He's out.

18:39.244 --> 18:40.829
So we'll find him. Thank you.

18:42.247 --> 18:43.582
[buzzing]

18:48.003 --> 18:49.046
How about a refill?

18:49.796 --> 18:50.631
I'd love one.

18:52.883 --> 18:53.717
[knock on door]

18:55.427 --> 18:56.929
I wanna thank you, man.

18:56.929 --> 18:57.888
MAL:
No need to thank me.

18:57.888 --> 19:01.725
It was a bullshit charge
and I'm just not down with bullshit.

19:02.893 --> 19:03.894
Can I come in for a second?

19:09.358 --> 19:10.317
Uh--

19:15.072 --> 19:17.407
I was hoping you might
let me stay for a couple days.

19:17.407 --> 19:18.659
You know, just till I get--

19:20.661 --> 19:24.540
No. I just didn't wanna be
a burden on Paige, you know.

19:26.124 --> 19:29.294
I get it. I'm sorry, but no.

19:29.294 --> 19:31.421
Edwin, I'm your caseworker,
I'm not your friend.

19:32.172 --> 19:33.715
You know, I was thinking
we were almost kinfolk.

19:36.051 --> 19:36.885
MAL:
We were.

19:37.469 --> 19:39.471
But not anymore.

19:40.556 --> 19:41.640
You okay, man?

19:42.224 --> 19:43.225
[Mal inhales shakily]

19:44.434 --> 19:45.352
No.

19:46.770 --> 19:48.522
No, I'm not okay,

19:48.522 --> 19:51.358
because I broke
the number one rule of my job.

19:51.358 --> 19:53.610
I got personally involved with a client,

19:53.610 --> 19:55.070
and my clients
are not the kind of people

19:55.070 --> 19:56.697
that you wanna be personally involved with

19:56.697 --> 19:58.574
because hurt people

19:59.616 --> 20:00.826
hurt people.

20:02.244 --> 20:03.579
She ended it, didn't she?

20:04.705 --> 20:05.622
Yeah.

20:06.582 --> 20:09.877
She ended it, but not because of me.

20:10.836 --> 20:12.296
You know why she ended it?

20:13.547 --> 20:16.300
Because she can't
take in the love of a good man.

20:17.301 --> 20:19.219
She doesn't recognize it
walking down the street.

20:19.219 --> 20:20.554
And you know why?

20:20.554 --> 20:22.556
Because she’s never
goddamn seen it before.

20:22.556 --> 20:23.849
And you know why?

20:23.849 --> 20:26.185
Because you abandoned her
when she was three years old.

20:26.185 --> 20:28.562
And then you kept on abandoning her.

20:28.562 --> 20:29.813
And then every time you took her back,

20:29.813 --> 20:31.857
you taught her that men
are unreliable,

20:31.857 --> 20:33.692
untrustworthy, and selfish.

20:33.692 --> 20:37.529
That they will continue to use her
to feel good about themselves

20:37.529 --> 20:39.072
and hurt her and leave her.

20:39.072 --> 20:40.073
That is what you did.

20:40.073 --> 20:41.783
And now she is paying the price.

20:43.952 --> 20:44.870
And so am I.

20:46.955 --> 20:49.041
I ain't got no excuses, man.

20:51.668 --> 20:52.544
Um--

20:53.670 --> 20:56.840
I don't have anyone to blame but myself.

20:57.508 --> 20:58.717
I should have known better.

21:00.594 --> 21:02.262
I should leave, man.

21:02.262 --> 21:03.138
Yep.

21:06.225 --> 21:07.768
If you wanna stay at the halfway house,

21:07.768 --> 21:10.354
legally I'm required to take you in,

21:11.480 --> 21:13.398
- but it's up to you.
- No, no. It's okay.

21:16.527 --> 21:17.736
Thank you for everything.

21:18.862 --> 21:19.738
Yeah.

21:25.452 --> 21:27.704
♪

21:33.001 --> 21:36.088
Paige, don't worry. Don't worry. I just--
I won't be here but a minute.

21:36.088 --> 21:39.550
I'm just gonna get a few of my things
and then I'll be out.

21:41.343 --> 21:42.386
Come in.

21:47.015 --> 21:47.891
You okay?

21:50.060 --> 21:51.186
Yeah, baby.

21:52.312 --> 21:54.231
No. I'm alright.

21:54.940 --> 21:57.401
I was just a little bit worried.

21:58.986 --> 21:59.820
Yeah.

22:00.445 --> 22:01.488
Paige, look here.

22:04.074 --> 22:07.202
I know how hard
the last 24 hours have been for you.

22:08.787 --> 22:11.665
And the fact that you
went through all that 'cause of me--

22:12.791 --> 22:15.210
But I promise you,

22:15.669 --> 22:17.421
you won't go through that ever again.

22:18.255 --> 22:20.465
I'll just get my things and Imma move out.

22:20.883 --> 22:22.509
Where are you going?

22:23.010 --> 22:24.845
I-I got a spot. For now.

22:26.346 --> 22:27.347
Paige, I--

22:27.806 --> 22:32.644
I never should have let you open up
your home to me in the first place.

22:32.644 --> 22:34.229
I shouldn't have put you in that position.

22:34.980 --> 22:36.190
I wasn't ready.

22:36.190 --> 22:39.276
I hadn't proved to myself
that I could stay out of trouble.

22:39.276 --> 22:40.444
FINN:
You didn't do anything.

22:40.444 --> 22:42.738
Well, wait now. That's-that's not true.

22:43.655 --> 22:47.034
Now I'm sitting in that jail cell
and I'm realizing, right,

22:47.034 --> 22:50.245
that everything I have done
up to this point

22:50.245 --> 22:52.748
- leads me right back to that jail cell.
- Not true.

22:52.748 --> 22:54.583
